{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"algophobic-pancreatic-louse","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\nThe GitHub CodeQL \"Security and quality\" scan flags `py/clear-text-logging-sensitive-data` in\n`docs/experiments/workflow-remediation-pocs/runtime_pydanticai_poc.py` (code-scanning alerts 3 and 4).\nThat file is a hand-run proof-of-concept: it is not packaged (the wheel/sdist ship only `src/rebar` —\n`pyproject.toml:213`), is on no `import rebar` path, and never runs in production. The findings are\nfalse positives (they log public provider-name strings such as \"anthropic\"/\"openai\", not secrets). The\nindividual alerts have been dismissed, but any code under `docs/` keeps generating recurring scan noise\non every push. The advanced-setup CodeQL workflow (`.github/workflows/codeql.yml`) currently passes no\nconfig, so nothing is excluded.\n\n## What\nAdd a CodeQL config file that excludes `docs/**` from analysis and wire it into the workflow, so the\nexclusion is durable (survives future `docs/experiments` additions) rather than relying on per-alert\ndismissals.\n- New file `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` with `paths-ignore: [\"docs/**\"]`.\n- Edit `.github/workflows/codeql.yml`: pass `config-file: ./.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` to the\n  `github/codeql-action/init` step. No change to the default query suite (only path scoping).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` exists and contains `paths-ignore` covering `docs/**`.\n- The CodeQL workflow's `init` step references that config file.\n- The change is config/workflow only — no shipped code under `src/rebar` is modified, so there is no\n  runtime behavior change.\n- On a subsequent scan, files under `docs/` are not analyzed and alerts 3/4 do not regenerate.\n\n## Out of scope\n- The 27 valid `py/path-injection` findings and the `py/stack-trace-exposure` finding (alert 27): those\n  need real code fixes and are tracked separately.","id":"5b57-96cf-7147-43ea","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":["security","codeql","ci"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"CodeQL: exclude docs/** from scanning (suppress unshipped-POC false positives)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784349980302357001,"uuid":"d3479e04-64ee-4bda-8c9c-ada49923a0e0"}